1
00:00:00,500 --> 00:00:01,300
[FAUCET SQUEAKING]

2
00:00:01,433 --> 00:00:04,133
Water's out again at this hour.

3
00:00:05,567 --> 00:00:09,633
[WATER RUNNING]

4
00:00:09,767 --> 00:00:12,267
<i> Let go of me!</i>

5
00:00:12,400 --> 00:00:14,133
Luna, you're not going with him!

6
00:00:14,267 --> 00:00:15,567
<i> Why do you even care?</i>

7
00:00:15,700 --> 00:00:17,133
<i> You think I'm afraid of you?</i>

8
00:00:17,267 --> 00:00:18,633
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [LUNA SCREAMS]

9
00:00:18,767 --> 00:00:19,667
[GRUNTS]

10
00:00:19,800 --> 00:00:21,833
<i> Gio! Peter!</i>

11
00:00:21,967 --> 00:00:24,733
<i>- Stop it! Please!
- Aah!</i>

12
00:00:24,867 --> 00:00:26,267
<i> Peter...</i>

13
00:00:27,167 --> 00:00:28,533
[MARTIN]
<i> Security, stop them!</i>

14
00:00:28,667 --> 00:00:31,400
[PETER]<i> Don't you dare call
</i> the cops! I'll kill you all!

15
00:00:31,533 --> 00:00:33,500
[MARTIN]
<i> Security, go after him!</i>

16
00:00:35,100 --> 00:00:37,167
<i> What's this place?</i>

17
00:00:41,033 --> 00:00:43,133
<i> - Who are you?
</i>- [BLADE SLICING FLESH]

18
00:00:44,100 --> 00:00:45,433
[BODY THUDS]

19
00:00:50,167 --> 00:00:54,933
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

20
00:00:55,067 --> 00:00:57,000
We can't find him anywhere.

21
00:00:57,133 --> 00:01:01,267
He could be swimming
to an island or hiding.

22
00:01:01,400 --> 00:01:03,267
He might be far by now.

23
00:01:03,400 --> 00:01:06,900
But he doesn't know
the area to get away that fast.

24
00:01:07,033 --> 00:01:10,133
- What about you, sir?
- Nothing.

25
00:01:10,300 --> 00:01:12,200
We've searched the whole area.

26
00:01:12,333 --> 00:01:15,433
So he's not
on hotel grounds anymore?

27
00:01:15,567 --> 00:01:17,067
He's gone.

28
00:01:17,200 --> 00:01:20,533
But don't worry,
we won't stop searching.

29
00:01:20,667 --> 00:01:24,167
We'll leave some officers
here at your hotel.

30
00:01:25,133 --> 00:01:27,900
- Alright. Thank you.
- Thank you, ma'am.

31
00:01:28,033 --> 00:01:34,733
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

32
00:01:39,767 --> 00:01:46,533
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

33
00:02:39,300 --> 00:02:40,633
[GIO] Luna.

34
00:02:42,900 --> 00:02:44,100
Luna!

35
00:02:44,233 --> 00:02:47,033
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

36
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:48,533
Luna!

37
00:02:51,900 --> 00:02:54,167
Luna, where are you going?

38
00:02:54,300 --> 00:02:56,233
Gio, I have so much work to do.

39
00:02:56,367 --> 00:02:58,733
For heaven's sake, Luna,
still work?

40
00:02:58,867 --> 00:03:04,367
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

41
00:03:04,500 --> 00:03:05,867
I have so many questions.

42
00:03:08,067 --> 00:03:10,367
So many,
I don't know where to start.

43
00:03:13,233 --> 00:03:14,700
He's my ex.

44
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:19,200
Peter.

45
00:03:22,900 --> 00:03:26,567
I wasn't two-timing you guys.
He came first.

46
00:03:27,867 --> 00:03:30,633
<i>What? You're going?
You're actually leaving me?!</i>

47
00:03:30,767 --> 00:03:34,033
<i>After all I did,
you just walk away?</i>

48
00:03:34,167 --> 00:03:35,967
<i> You're not leaving!</i>

49
00:03:36,100 --> 00:03:40,667
<i>I love you, Peter, but
I won't let you ruin my life!</i>

50
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:42,600
<i> Your life's been ruined!</i>

51
00:03:42,733 --> 00:03:46,300
<i>You were a mess
when I met you.</i>

52
00:03:46,433 --> 00:03:49,500
<i> You're no different from me!</i>

53
00:03:49,633 --> 00:03:51,633
[BREATH SHAKING]

54
00:03:51,767 --> 00:03:55,933
<i>Don't compare me to you.
We are different!</i>

55
00:03:56,100 --> 00:03:58,567
<i> I left home to be with you!</i>

56
00:04:00,667 --> 00:04:05,267
<i>Loving you
was my biggest mistake.</i>

57
00:04:06,333 --> 00:04:07,933
<i> But what about you?</i>

58
00:04:08,067 --> 00:04:09,733
<i>What about me?!
Go on, tell me!</i>

59
00:04:09,867 --> 00:04:13,333
<i>You didn't just leave!
You were kicked out!</i>

60
00:04:13,467 --> 00:04:16,200
<i> Disowned for your crap!</i>

61
00:04:16,333 --> 00:04:18,933
<i> Gambling, drugs, women...</i>

62
00:04:19,067 --> 00:04:22,500
Do I have to list every secret?

63
00:04:22,633 --> 00:04:24,767
<i>No wonder you had
so much money!</i>

64
00:04:24,900 --> 00:04:26,133
<i> So?</i>

65
00:04:26,267 --> 00:04:27,800
<i> You benefited too, didn't you?</i>

66
00:04:27,967 --> 00:04:31,000
<i>Because I didn't know
it was dirty!</i>

67
00:04:31,133 --> 00:04:35,233
<i> Who would believe you?! Huh?</i>

68
00:04:35,367 --> 00:04:38,133
<i> Go on! Say it!</i>

69
00:04:38,267 --> 00:04:39,833
<i> You're such a hypocrite!</i>

70
00:04:39,967 --> 00:04:43,833
<i>You lied to me.
You tricked me over and over!</i>

71
00:04:44,967 --> 00:04:48,100
You won't drag me down anymore.
<i> I'm leaving you.</i>

72
00:04:48,233 --> 00:04:50,767
<i>Fine. Go then.
You're leaving?</i>

73
00:04:50,900 --> 00:04:54,000
<i>- Let go me! Let go of me!
- Fine, get out!</i>

74
00:04:56,067 --> 00:04:57,667
<i> Don't you ever come back!</i>

75
00:04:57,800 --> 00:05:01,700
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

76
00:05:01,867 --> 00:05:04,700
<i>I have absolutely no intention
of ever coming back to you!</i>

77
00:05:04,833 --> 00:05:09,100
[HEAVY RAIN POURING]

78
00:05:09,233 --> 00:05:11,333
<i> Hello?
</i>Please, even just a little bit.

79
00:05:11,467 --> 00:05:13,600
<i>I just need a place
to stay tonight.</i>

80
00:05:14,633 --> 00:05:16,767
<i> What?</i>

81
00:05:16,900 --> 00:05:18,600
<i> Oh? Okay, thanks anyway.</i>

82
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:24,633
<i> Hello?</i>

83
00:05:24,767 --> 00:05:27,400
<i> Mae? It's Luna.</i>

84
00:05:27,533 --> 00:05:29,433
<i> Can you spare some?</i>

85
00:05:31,300 --> 00:05:34,733
<i> Hello? Hello?</i>

86
00:05:34,900 --> 00:05:37,267
<i> Hello? Hello?</i>

87
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:44,067
- [HEAVY RAIN POURING]
- [POIGNANT MUSIC PLAYING]

88
00:05:46,133 --> 00:05:48,467
[LINE DISCONNECTS]

89
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:55,000
[POIGNANT MUSIC CONTINUES]

90
00:05:55,133 --> 00:05:56,633
[SNIFFLES]

91
00:06:04,833 --> 00:06:05,867
[SNIFFLES]

92
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:10,767
[POIGNANT MUSIC CONTINUES]

93
00:06:10,933 --> 00:06:13,833
[WHIMPERS]

94
00:06:16,333 --> 00:06:22,700
[HORN BLARING]

95
00:06:35,100 --> 00:06:41,867
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC PLAYING]

96
00:06:48,967 --> 00:06:53,933
[SOBBING]

97
00:06:54,067 --> 00:06:59,167
[EMOTIONAL MUSIC CONTINUES]

98
00:06:59,300 --> 00:07:01,467
<i>- Same spot?
- Same spot.</i>

99
00:07:03,133 --> 00:07:04,967
I wish it was always like this.

100
00:07:06,367 --> 00:07:07,600
[GIO] What are we?

101
00:07:07,733 --> 00:07:09,467
[LUNA] We're like a bridge.

102
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:11,333
[GIO]
<i> What are you talking about?</i>

103
00:07:11,467 --> 00:07:13,700
<i>- I mean, our status right now.
- [GIO] Mm.</i>

104
00:07:13,833 --> 00:07:17,433
[LUNA]
<i> Like we're on opposite ends.</i>

105
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:19,100
[GIO] Oh, like the saying?

106
00:07:19,233 --> 00:07:21,967
<i>That... we'll cross the bridge
when we get there.</i>

107
00:07:22,100 --> 00:07:23,233
[LUNA CHUCKLING]

108
00:07:23,367 --> 00:07:25,333
[LUNA]
<i> We will cross the bridge...</i>

109
00:07:25,467 --> 00:07:28,067
when we're ready for each other.

110
00:07:29,533 --> 00:07:32,367
- [LUNA]<i> Are you ready?
</i>- [GIO] Always have been.

111
00:07:32,500 --> 00:07:34,000
[GIO] What about you?
Are you ready?

112
00:07:35,100 --> 00:07:38,033
[DOG BARKING]

113
00:07:43,233 --> 00:07:45,933
[PETER] Luna. Luna.

114
00:07:47,333 --> 00:07:50,233
<i> Luna. Luna.</i>

115
00:07:50,400 --> 00:07:52,033
<i> What are you doing, Peter?</i>

116
00:07:52,167 --> 00:07:55,333
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

117
00:07:55,467 --> 00:07:59,767
<i> I knew it. You still love me.</i>

118
00:07:59,900 --> 00:08:02,000
<i>You've got a lot of nerve
threatening me.</i>

119
00:08:02,133 --> 00:08:03,800
<i> I'm not threatening you.</i>

120
00:08:03,933 --> 00:08:07,000
<i>I mean it. I'll kill myself
if you don't show up.</i>

121
00:08:07,133 --> 00:08:09,467
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

122
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:12,400
<i> Come with me. Let's run away.</i>

123
00:08:12,533 --> 00:08:14,733
<i> Just be with me. Luna...</i>

124
00:08:14,867 --> 00:08:19,100
<i>I'm not going with you.
Don't ever contact me again.</i>

125
00:08:20,300 --> 00:08:21,667
<i> It's over between us.</i>

126
00:08:22,767 --> 00:08:24,333
<i> Please get your life together.</i>

127
00:08:24,467 --> 00:08:28,367
<i>It's not over between us, and
I'm never letting it be over!</i>

128
00:08:28,500 --> 00:08:30,167
<i>I'm so done with you, Peter.
It's over!</i>

129
00:08:30,300 --> 00:08:31,867
<i>- Luna!
- I'm done!</i>

130
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:34,067
<i>- Luna, don't leave me!
- I said I'm done, Peter!</i>

131
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:35,500
<i>- I've had enough!
- Don't leave me!</i>

132
00:08:35,633 --> 00:08:36,900
<i> I can't do this anymore!</i>

133
00:08:37,033 --> 00:08:38,867
<i> - Luna!</i> [GUNSHOTS]
- [LUNA SCREAMS]

134
00:08:39,933 --> 00:08:42,000
<i>- Peter! Peter!
- Fine, I'll kill myself.</i>

135
00:08:42,133 --> 00:08:43,033
<i> Don't-- Stop!</i>

136
00:08:43,167 --> 00:08:44,567
<i>Give me what I want,
or I'll kill myself.</i>

137
00:08:44,700 --> 00:08:47,167
<i>- Don't do that! Please!
- Luna, I want to die!</i>

138
00:08:47,300 --> 00:08:48,400
<i> Please, no!</i>

139
00:08:48,533 --> 00:08:52,400
- [GUNSHOTS]
- [MUFFLED VOICE] Stop it!

140
00:08:52,533 --> 00:08:56,533
- [SOBBING]
- [BREATHING HEAVILY]

141
00:08:56,700 --> 00:09:03,600
- [HIGH-PITCHED RINGING]
- [GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

142
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:08,333
<i> Peter, you shot the kid.</i>

143
00:09:08,467 --> 00:09:10,167
<i> Peter, the kid...</i>

144
00:09:11,567 --> 00:09:13,333
<i> Peter...</i>

145
00:09:13,467 --> 00:09:15,400
<i> Peter!</i> [SOBS LOUDLY]

146
00:09:15,533 --> 00:09:17,067
<i> Peter!</i>

147
00:09:18,567 --> 00:09:20,333
<i> P-Peter!</i>

148
00:09:20,467 --> 00:09:21,700
<i> Wait...</i>

149
00:09:22,367 --> 00:09:25,133
<i> Help! Help!</i>

150
00:09:25,633 --> 00:09:27,100
Peter... [SOBS]

151
00:09:27,233 --> 00:09:29,200
<i> Help! Help!</i>

152
00:09:29,367 --> 00:09:32,000
<i> The kid... Somebody help!</i>

153
00:09:32,500 --> 00:09:34,967
<i> Help!</i>

154
00:09:35,100 --> 00:09:38,600
[SOBBING]

155
00:09:38,733 --> 00:09:42,667
<i> Help! Peter!</i>

156
00:09:44,767 --> 00:09:47,133
[LUNA] Dad went to see me
at the police station.

157
00:09:49,200 --> 00:09:50,400
Dad saved me.

158
00:09:50,533 --> 00:09:53,867
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

159
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:54,900
[LUNA] Dad...

160
00:09:55,967 --> 00:09:56,833
<i> Dad...</i>

161
00:09:58,067 --> 00:09:58,967
<i> Dad...</i>

162
00:09:59,400 --> 00:10:01,100
[SOBBING]

163
00:10:01,267 --> 00:10:02,333
<i> Dad...</i>

164
00:10:02,467 --> 00:10:04,833
[LUNA] Dad saved me
from that life.

165
00:10:05,800 --> 00:10:07,833
A life that I don't want
to go back to.

166
00:10:12,267 --> 00:10:13,800
Why didn't you tell me?

167
00:10:13,933 --> 00:10:14,967
What for?

168
00:10:16,700 --> 00:10:19,133
To drag you into
my messy life?

169
00:10:21,933 --> 00:10:25,333
Gio, I loved you.
I loved you so much.

170
00:10:26,700 --> 00:10:28,767
I couldn't do that to you.

171
00:10:30,667 --> 00:10:32,067
I can't.

172
00:10:32,200 --> 00:10:38,833
[POIGNANT MUSIC PLAYING]

173
00:10:42,333 --> 00:10:43,900
I can do it.

174
00:10:44,367 --> 00:10:46,000
I know, but...

175
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:47,367
Just let me do this.

176
00:10:48,900 --> 00:10:49,967
Just for now.

177
00:10:51,767 --> 00:10:52,733
Luna...

178
00:10:52,933 --> 00:10:54,767
I know I'm being annoying,

179
00:10:54,767 --> 00:10:56,833
but are you sure you're alright?

180
00:10:57,067 --> 00:10:59,133
Shouldn't we take you
to the hospital?

181
00:11:01,033 --> 00:11:03,433
I'm okay.
I don't want to bother everyone.

182
00:11:04,400 --> 00:11:06,833
Kiko said they're
still searching for Peter.

183
00:11:08,067 --> 00:11:10,933
The cops won't stop
until they find the bastard.

184
00:11:11,300 --> 00:11:13,533
And Leon added some security.

185
00:11:14,200 --> 00:11:18,233
He won't be able to come
near you or us again.

186
00:11:21,333 --> 00:11:22,533
I just realized...

187
00:11:24,967 --> 00:11:26,500
Whatever we do,

188
00:11:28,567 --> 00:11:32,000
the past just keeps
catching up to us.

189
00:11:33,900 --> 00:11:35,133
We can't...

190
00:11:35,500 --> 00:11:37,267
seem to escape it at all.

191
00:11:38,533 --> 00:11:45,467
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

192
00:11:57,433 --> 00:11:59,233
Oh...

193
00:11:59,833 --> 00:12:02,133
So, that's why you act that way
with Luna.

194
00:12:02,567 --> 00:12:04,867
I thought you're just mad
for no reason.

195
00:12:04,867 --> 00:12:06,200
It all makes sense now.

196
00:12:07,333 --> 00:12:09,533
What happens now?

197
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:11,533
I don't know.

198
00:12:11,933 --> 00:12:13,800
[KIKO] What do you mean
you don't know?

199
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:16,300
We're all co-workers.

200
00:12:16,533 --> 00:12:18,400
You're going to see
each other every day.

201
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:24,833
All I know is... [EXHALES]

202
00:12:26,333 --> 00:12:28,900
I want to be mad at her, too.

203
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:34,900
I want to be mad
that she didn't tell me

204
00:12:37,033 --> 00:12:39,933
why she never gave me a chance
to decide for myself.

205
00:12:41,500 --> 00:12:42,533
[SIGHS]

206
00:12:43,567 --> 00:12:46,533
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

207
00:12:53,333 --> 00:12:55,300
Did she really think
I wouldn't understand?

208
00:13:01,133 --> 00:13:03,333
Did she think I'm that weak?

209
00:13:06,433 --> 00:13:07,967
I want to get angry, but--

210
00:13:07,967 --> 00:13:09,467
[MARTIN] But you can't.

211
00:13:09,467 --> 00:13:11,300
Because you still love her.

212
00:13:12,567 --> 00:13:19,500
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

213
00:13:36,567 --> 00:13:37,567
Luna.

214
00:13:38,433 --> 00:13:39,900
You're going to work?

215
00:13:40,233 --> 00:13:41,167
Yeah.

216
00:13:41,400 --> 00:13:42,633
Why shouldn't I?

217
00:13:43,333 --> 00:13:45,567
Sir, are you also
getting breakfast?

218
00:13:46,167 --> 00:13:47,567
No. Just water.

219
00:13:48,333 --> 00:13:51,133
[LUNA] If I don't go to work,
what would I do in here?

220
00:13:51,533 --> 00:13:52,933
Sulk around?

221
00:13:53,467 --> 00:13:54,567
Cry?

222
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:56,200
Take a rest.

223
00:13:57,600 --> 00:13:58,533
No.

224
00:13:58,533 --> 00:14:00,333
I don't want to be alone
with my thoughts.

225
00:14:03,433 --> 00:14:05,300
Anyway, you can
go back to work, too.

226
00:14:05,300 --> 00:14:06,633
I'm lifting your suspension.

227
00:14:07,033 --> 00:14:08,600
I think you've learned
your lesson.

228
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:11,067
Not now. I need to do
something important.

229
00:14:11,067 --> 00:14:13,033
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYS]

230
00:14:13,033 --> 00:14:14,967
Is hanging around important?

231
00:14:16,600 --> 00:14:18,200
Think what you want, Luna.

232
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:21,467
But I need to do
what I need to do.

233
00:14:24,567 --> 00:14:25,567
I should get going.

234
00:14:26,333 --> 00:14:27,433
Take care at work.

235
00:14:34,500 --> 00:14:36,467
How was your flight, Auntie?

236
00:14:36,467 --> 00:14:38,700
It's fine, save from a jet lag,

237
00:14:38,700 --> 00:14:41,000
but I'm still here for you.

238
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:42,067
Thank you.

239
00:14:42,400 --> 00:14:44,267
I like your hotel, Martin.

240
00:14:44,267 --> 00:14:45,433
I like the vibe.

241
00:14:45,700 --> 00:14:49,033
Very homey, welcoming,

242
00:14:49,033 --> 00:14:50,467
and not intimidating.

243
00:14:51,600 --> 00:14:53,767
- Hello, Philippines!
- And hello, world!

244
00:14:53,767 --> 00:14:55,667
Welcome to Hotel 88!

245
00:14:55,667 --> 00:14:57,400
The hotel that used to be
an evictee,

246
00:14:57,400 --> 00:15:00,033
but is now a returnee!

247
00:15:00,333 --> 00:15:01,700
How are you, everyone?

248
00:15:02,167 --> 00:15:04,567
[MARTIN] Uncle, they're
our helpers around the hotel.

249
00:15:04,567 --> 00:15:06,167
This is Raphie and Monette.

250
00:15:06,167 --> 00:15:08,367
They're our longest
employees here.

251
00:15:08,367 --> 00:15:10,400
[MONETTE]
We basically grew up here.

252
00:15:10,400 --> 00:15:11,733
Nice to meet you, sir!

253
00:15:11,733 --> 00:15:13,200
[RONALD] Nice to meet you, too.

254
00:15:13,200 --> 00:15:14,600
[CARMELA] Nice to meet you.

255
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:16,667
- Ah! Drinks?
- Oh, thank you.

256
00:15:16,667 --> 00:15:18,100
- Drinks, ma'am?
- Thank you.

257
00:15:18,100 --> 00:15:19,567
- Thank you.
- You're welcome!

258
00:15:20,067 --> 00:15:22,133
And this is Leon Almazan.

259
00:15:22,133 --> 00:15:23,233
Good morning, sir.

260
00:15:23,467 --> 00:15:24,800
Nice to meet you.

261
00:15:24,800 --> 00:15:26,500
Uh, where are the other
Almazans?

262
00:15:26,500 --> 00:15:27,767
They're on their way.

263
00:15:29,267 --> 00:15:31,500
And they are my brothers.

264
00:15:31,500 --> 00:15:35,067
[MARTIN] This is Kiko Endaya
and Gio Cabrera.

265
00:15:36,333 --> 00:15:37,367
- Ah.
- Sir.

266
00:15:39,133 --> 00:15:41,067
You have different surnames?

267
00:15:41,067 --> 00:15:42,100
[KIKO] Yes, sir.

268
00:15:42,100 --> 00:15:45,167
We have the same father,
but different mothers.

269
00:15:45,533 --> 00:15:49,500
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

270
00:15:49,800 --> 00:15:52,300
Isn't that nice, sir?

271
00:15:52,300 --> 00:15:54,700
Even though
they have different mothers,

272
00:15:54,700 --> 00:15:57,533
they still got along so well!

273
00:15:57,533 --> 00:15:59,733
[SARI]
And now, they're a solid bunch!

274
00:16:02,200 --> 00:16:04,200
Martin, can I see
the other areas?

275
00:16:04,200 --> 00:16:06,133
Of course, Uncle.
This way, please.

276
00:16:08,167 --> 00:16:09,633
- Have fun.
- Nice to meet you, sir.

277
00:16:10,400 --> 00:16:17,333
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

278
00:16:22,733 --> 00:16:24,467
So, how have you been?

279
00:16:24,467 --> 00:16:26,433
Edward told me what happened.

280
00:16:26,433 --> 00:16:28,500
[CHUCKLES]
Don't worry about me, Uncle.

281
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:30,100
I'm always okay.

282
00:16:30,700 --> 00:16:32,533
Thank you for coming over.

283
00:16:33,400 --> 00:16:35,133
I'm just here
to catch up on things.

284
00:16:35,700 --> 00:16:37,333
Thank you for the concern,

285
00:16:37,867 --> 00:16:39,800
and for all your help.

286
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:44,700
Well, my only concern is your
and your siblings' well-being.

287
00:16:45,633 --> 00:16:47,133
Especially now...

288
00:16:47,567 --> 00:16:48,767
that Fred is gone.

289
00:16:49,567 --> 00:16:51,100
It's all so good, Martin.

290
00:16:51,500 --> 00:16:53,133
We have a lot to talk about.

291
00:16:53,133 --> 00:16:55,200
- That's good news, Uncle.
- [CHUCKLES]

292
00:16:57,467 --> 00:17:00,433
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYS]

293
00:17:03,467 --> 00:17:04,667
Mr. Arellano.

294
00:17:06,233 --> 00:17:07,267
Luna.

295
00:17:08,467 --> 00:17:10,600
This is Mr. Ronald Lucero.

296
00:17:10,600 --> 00:17:12,867
And his wife,
Mrs. Carmela Lucero.

297
00:17:13,700 --> 00:17:16,367
This is Luna Almazan,
our general manager.

298
00:17:17,400 --> 00:17:19,367
- Good morning, sir.
- Nice to meet you.

299
00:17:20,233 --> 00:17:22,500
- And this is Mr. Andy--
- Arellano.

300
00:17:23,467 --> 00:17:24,600
I know who he is.

301
00:17:26,600 --> 00:17:29,267
A businessman's world
is not a huge one.

302
00:17:29,600 --> 00:17:32,300
I see there are other people
interested in your hotel.

303
00:17:32,300 --> 00:17:33,767
Yes, Mr. Lucero.

304
00:17:33,767 --> 00:17:35,300
Is there a problem?

305
00:17:36,333 --> 00:17:37,800
The more, the merrier, right?

306
00:17:38,700 --> 00:17:45,633
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

307
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:52,967
[ANDY] So, how's your day?

308
00:17:52,967 --> 00:17:54,533
[EMPLOYEE] We're alright, sir.

309
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:57,633
[ANDY] Get some rest
if you're tired.

310
00:17:57,633 --> 00:17:58,833
You can't get sick.

311
00:17:58,833 --> 00:18:00,700
[EMPLOYEE] Yes, sir. Thank you.

312
00:18:00,700 --> 00:18:07,600
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

313
00:18:21,300 --> 00:18:28,233
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

314
00:18:30,133 --> 00:18:36,100
[PHONE RINGING]

315
00:18:42,200 --> 00:18:45,367
[RINGING CONTINUES]

316
00:18:45,367 --> 00:18:47,133
[PHONE BEEPS]

317
00:18:50,233 --> 00:18:52,267
[ANDY ON THE PHONE]
<i> Stop with your games already.</i>

318
00:18:54,867 --> 00:18:56,367
<i> I need you, Sandro.</i>

319
00:18:58,367 --> 00:19:00,733
<i>Other people want
to enter Hotel 88,</i>

320
00:19:00,733 --> 00:19:02,233
<i> and I can't let that happen.</i>

321
00:19:02,233 --> 00:19:03,700
<i> You know why.</i>

322
00:19:04,867 --> 00:19:07,233
You need to act
before it's too late.

323
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:11,167
Are you listening?

324
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:15,833
[PHONE BEEPS]

325
00:19:15,833 --> 00:19:17,267
Answer me, San--

326
00:19:17,267 --> 00:19:19,300
Hello? Hello?

327
00:19:19,300 --> 00:19:26,267
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

328
00:19:28,767 --> 00:19:33,900
"I will..."

329
00:19:40,933 --> 00:19:41,933
[PHONE CHIMES]

330
00:19:43,933 --> 00:19:50,867
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

331
00:19:58,767 --> 00:20:01,933
"I will handle it.

332
00:20:09,933 --> 00:20:13,400
Our projections require
a significant capital, Uncle.

333
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:15,367
That's why we're
bringing you two in.

334
00:20:15,367 --> 00:20:16,833
I know Andy.

335
00:20:17,467 --> 00:20:20,333
He doesn't have
a good reputation in business.

336
00:20:20,333 --> 00:20:22,733
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

337
00:20:22,733 --> 00:20:24,100
What do you mean?

338
00:20:26,867 --> 00:20:28,867
I don't want to expand
on what I know.

339
00:20:30,333 --> 00:20:31,967
But one thing is for sure.

340
00:20:33,433 --> 00:20:37,400
I won't join this venture
if he is involved.

341
00:20:38,067 --> 00:20:41,500
I can put in the same amount
Andy Arellano would.

342
00:20:41,500 --> 00:20:42,433
But, Uncle...

343
00:20:42,433 --> 00:20:44,967
It's either me or Andy Arellano.

344
00:20:44,967 --> 00:20:51,800
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

345
00:20:55,467 --> 00:20:56,933
[ANDY] Hello?

346
00:20:56,933 --> 00:20:58,167
Can you hear me?

347
00:20:59,900 --> 00:21:00,933
Hello?

348
00:21:02,167 --> 00:21:03,800
Hello? You're breaking up.

349
00:21:05,333 --> 00:21:06,367
[SCOFFS]

350
00:21:06,367 --> 00:21:09,367
Are you kidding me?
Where's Sandro's phone?

351
00:21:12,033 --> 00:21:14,300
He's not answering
or replying.

352
00:21:15,100 --> 00:21:16,167
And if it was Sandro,

353
00:21:16,167 --> 00:21:18,067
I'm sure what I said
would've made him nervous.

354
00:21:18,067 --> 00:21:20,300
But he's not answering my calls.

355
00:21:21,233 --> 00:21:22,900
Yes, he replied to me,

356
00:21:22,900 --> 00:21:24,433
but he didn't speak
when I called.

357
00:21:26,167 --> 00:21:28,367
If none of you
have his phone,

358
00:21:29,300 --> 00:21:30,900
someone else took it.

359
00:21:31,833 --> 00:21:33,233
I hope my hunch is wrong.

360
00:21:33,233 --> 00:21:34,900
I want you to look into it.

361
00:21:41,067 --> 00:21:47,967
- [UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]
- [FLIES BUZZING]

362
00:22:02,233 --> 00:22:03,367
[LOUD THUD]

363
00:22:04,367 --> 00:22:05,467
Did you hear that?

364
00:22:06,100 --> 00:22:07,067
[MARTIN] Heard what?

365
00:22:07,567 --> 00:22:09,233
There was a loud thud.

366
00:22:10,267 --> 00:22:12,133
It was faint, but it seemed like
it came from underground.

367
00:22:12,133 --> 00:22:14,333
[SIGHS] It's probably
just the staff cleaning.

368
00:22:14,333 --> 00:22:16,300
Can we focus for now, Kiko?

369
00:22:17,100 --> 00:22:18,367
Sorry.

370
00:22:18,367 --> 00:22:21,033
[SIGHS] Like I said,

371
00:22:21,033 --> 00:22:23,533
it's either Uncle Ronald
or Andy Arellano.

372
00:22:23,533 --> 00:22:25,833
We just have to pick one.

373
00:22:25,833 --> 00:22:27,833
You should pick your investor.

374
00:22:27,833 --> 00:22:29,933
Of course, I will. I worked hard
to convince him.

375
00:22:29,933 --> 00:22:32,233
And I trust Uncle Ronald more.

376
00:22:32,600 --> 00:22:34,433
I'll pick whoever you pick.

377
00:22:36,367 --> 00:22:38,000
How about you, Gio?

378
00:22:39,600 --> 00:22:42,233
Luna will get hurt
if we go against them again.

379
00:22:44,900 --> 00:22:45,933
Besides...

380
00:22:47,067 --> 00:22:48,467
she's going through a lot
right now.

381
00:22:49,433 --> 00:22:51,233
This will just add
to her burden.

382
00:22:53,333 --> 00:22:55,933
Well... I guess.

383
00:22:57,167 --> 00:23:00,000
Let's just pick whoever offers
the better investment terms.

384
00:23:00,867 --> 00:23:03,233
Mm. That's fairer.

385
00:23:04,333 --> 00:23:06,200
Right, Gio?

386
00:23:06,200 --> 00:23:09,633
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

387
00:23:09,633 --> 00:23:10,567
Mm.

388
00:23:18,700 --> 00:23:20,567
Can't you hear
what I'm saying?

389
00:23:20,700 --> 00:23:22,233
Peter is missing.

390
00:23:22,400 --> 00:23:25,167
He was last seen at Hotel 88.

391
00:23:25,900 --> 00:23:28,200
We know that's where
he was last seen.

392
00:23:29,100 --> 00:23:30,833
Because we're looking
for him too.

393
00:23:30,967 --> 00:23:33,867
So you already know.
Then where is he?!

394
00:23:34,000 --> 00:23:35,833
We still haven't found him.

395
00:23:35,967 --> 00:23:38,100
But our men will keep searching.

396
00:23:39,433 --> 00:23:42,100
Maybe you know where he is.

397
00:23:42,233 --> 00:23:43,333
Why me?

398
00:23:43,467 --> 00:23:45,300
Would I be here if I knew?!

399
00:23:46,267 --> 00:23:48,500
Sir, you need to find him.

400
00:23:48,633 --> 00:23:49,867
Of course we should.

401
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:51,733
He has to answer to the law.

402
00:23:52,300 --> 00:23:54,433
He's got a long list of cases
against him.

403
00:23:54,833 --> 00:23:56,433
Sir, he has my money.

404
00:23:56,600 --> 00:24:00,067
I need my money!
I need my money!

405
00:24:00,833 --> 00:24:02,333
Have you tried
contacting him?

406
00:24:04,167 --> 00:24:07,667
He's not replying
or answering my calls.

407
00:24:08,567 --> 00:24:09,700
Damn it.

408
00:24:10,600 --> 00:24:12,267
He might be running off
with my money.

409
00:24:12,400 --> 00:24:18,967
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

410
00:24:22,133 --> 00:24:29,133
- [MUSIC TURNS DARK]
- [WATER DRIPPING]

411
00:24:41,600 --> 00:24:48,333
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

412
00:24:55,700 --> 00:24:58,200
<i>They all went missing
at Hotel 88.</i>

413
00:24:58,333 --> 00:24:59,300
<i> I'll lead this case.</i>

414
00:24:59,433 --> 00:25:01,867
That is, if you trust me enough
<i> to handle it.</i>

415
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:04,367
<i>I want to know how you
became friends with my dad.</i>

416
00:25:04,533 --> 00:25:06,767
<i>You brought me to a secluded
area here in Hotel 88</i>

417
00:25:06,900 --> 00:25:08,100
<i> just to ask me that?</i>

418
00:25:08,233 --> 00:25:11,300
<i>Your life is in danger!
He's a dangerous man!</i>

419
00:25:11,433 --> 00:25:14,567
<i>If you don't tell her you
like her as more than a friend,</i>

420
00:25:14,700 --> 00:25:16,533
<i>you'll always be
just a friend in her life.</i>

421
00:25:16,667 --> 00:25:18,100
<i>Are you and Edward
in a relationship?</i>

422
00:25:19,467 --> 00:25:20,233
<i> Let's go.</i>

423
00:25:20,367 --> 00:25:21,533
<i>Where are you going
to take me?</i>

424
00:25:21,667 --> 00:25:23,133
<i> Just trust me on this one.</i>
